  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_3' aria-label=\" Dogiparthi Venkata Satish and Anr. versus Pilla Durga Prasad & Ors. pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('3','2025','2025_8_2191_2198','2025INSC1046'); ><font size='4'> <strong>DOGIPARTHI VENKATA SATISH AND ANR.<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>PILLA DURGA PRASAD & ORS. </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 8 S.C.R. 2191</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 1046</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010008492025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : VIKRAM NATH<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, SANDEEP MEHTA</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Whether Order XXX Rule 10 CPC in any manner debar a suit filed against the proprietor. Headnotes&dagger; Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 &ndash; Or. XXX, R.10 and Or. VII, R.11 &ndash; Appellant filed a suit for eviction &ndash; Defendant no.1 was Aditya Motors (the lessee), of PDP &ndash; An application was filed by appellant u/Or. VI, R.17 CPC seeking amendment of plaint &ndash; One of the amendments sought was that the lessee-defendant no.1 be deleted and, in its place, PDP be substituted as representative of the lessee &ndash; Amendment was allowed &ndash; After<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 26-08-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CIVIL APPEAL No. 11104/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Appeal(s) allowed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('3','2025','2025_8_2191_2198','2025INSC1046','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'